postcontent: Graham/Burlington area. NR Davis & Sons 100 year old working double barrel (side by side) with double triggers- 12 gauge shotgun. It's old and looks very good for its age. Still locks up tight, both triggers cock when barrel is opened, and both barrels fire their firing pins- Very solid feeling and operating shotgun. I've never shot it. These took a 2&1/2" standard sized 12 gauge shell I believe, but the powder or pressure was lighter back then. I don't believe a shotgun this age was designed for today's high pressure ammo. I would check it out thoroughly before using it and confirm what current ammo fits the original design pressure. Great vintage antique for the wall or to use with the correct 2&1/2" shells. Need the cash is reason for selling, as this one had a permanent spot decorating my wall.
